{{#IF_MEMORY}}## Memory Integration

**Before any plan**, search memories:
```bash
curl -s "{{MEMORY_API_BASE}}/memory/search?q=<TOPIC>&limit=10"
curl -s "{{MEMORY_API_BASE}}/memory/search?q=<FILE_NAMES>&category=gotcha&limit=5"
```

Every plan MUST include a `## Memory Context` section showing what was searched, what warnings exist, and how the plan accounts for past learnings. If no memories found, note "No relevant memories found for: '<query>'" to prove the search was attempted.

**During conversation**, capture learnings:
```bash
curl -s -X POST "{{MEMORY_API_BASE}}/memory/store" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"content": "<learning>", "category": "<category>", "tags": ["<tags>"], "sourceType": "manual", "sourceProject": "{{TRAQR_PROJECT_SLUG}}"}'
```
{{/IF_MEMORY}}

