## Plan Flow

### Stage 1: Meta-Plan (Approach Alignment)

Present approach options with pros/cons, recommend one, define scope (IN/OUT), identify risks.

### Stage 2: Detailed Plan (After Approach Approved)

Write plan to `memory/plans/YYYYMMDD-HHMM-<slug>.md` with:

```markdown
---
id: plan-YYYYMMDD-HHMM-<slug>
title: <Title>
status: approved
priority: P0 | P1 | P2 | P3
{{#IF_MEMORY}}confidence: 0.7
memory_id: null{{/IF_MEMORY}}
{{#IF_LINEAR}}linear_ticket: null{{/IF_LINEAR}}
{{#IF_GITHUB_ISSUES}}github_issue: null{{/IF_GITHUB_ISSUES}}
created: <ISO-8601>
dispatched: null
---

# Plan: <Title>

## Context
Why this change is needed.

{{#IF_MEMORY}}## Memory Context
Relevant past plans, searched learnings, warnings, how plan accounts for them.
{{/IF_MEMORY}}

## Changes
### 1. <Change>
**File**: `path/to/file.ts` — Action: create | modify | delete
<Implementation spec>

## Files Summary
| # | File | Action | Description |
|---|------|--------|-------------|

## Verification
How to test after implementation.

## Commit Message
<type>: <subject>
```

{{#IF_MEMORY}}### Store Plan in Vector DB

```bash
curl -s -X POST "{{MEMORY_API_BASE}}/memory/store" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"content": "<FULL_PLAN>", "summary": "<title>", "category": "pattern", "tags": ["plan"], "sourceType": "plan", "sourceRef": "plan-ID", "sourceProject": "{{TRAQR_PROJECT_SLUG}}"}'
```
{{/IF_MEMORY}}

{{#IF_PLAN_DISPATCH}}### Stage 3: Dispatch

On approval, immediately create ticket and dispatch. No implementation in analysis.
{{/IF_PLAN_DISPATCH}}

